      • TRN_FC_WSP_PATTERN

        static final Pattern TRN_FC_WSP_PATTERN
        Funnel Cloud (Tornadic activity_B/E(hh)mm_LOC/DIR_(MOV)). At manual stationS, tornadoes, funnel clouds, or waterspouts shall be coded in the format, TORNADIC ACTIVITY_B/E(hh)mm_LOC/DIR_(MOV)

      • AUTO_PATTERN

        static final Pattern AUTO_PATTERN
        Type of Automated Station (AO1 or AO2). AO1 or AO2 shall be coded in all METAR/SPECI from automated stations.

      • BEGIN_END_WEATHER_PATTERN

        static final Pattern BEGIN_END_WEATHER_PATTERN
        Beginning and End of Precipitation. Example RAB20E51

      • SEALVL_PRESS_PATTERN

        static final Pattern SEALVL_PRESS_PATTERN
        Sea-Level Pressure (SLPppp). At designated stations, the sea-level pressure shall be coded in the format SLPppp

      • PEAK_WIND_PATTERN

        static final Pattern PEAK_WIND_PATTERN
        Peak Wind (PK_WND_dddff(f)/(hh)mm). The peak wind shall be coded in the format, PK_WND_dddff(f)/(hh)mm of the next METAR

      • WIND_SHIFT_PATTERN

        static final Pattern WIND_SHIFT_PATTERN
        Wind Shift (WSHFT_(hh)mm). A wind shift shall be coded in the format WSHFT_(hh)mm

      • TWR_SFC_VIS_PATTERN

        static final Pattern TWR_SFC_VIS_PATTERN
        Tower or Surface Visibility (TWR_VIS_vvvvv or SFC_VIS_vvvvv). Tower visibility or surface visibility shall be coded in the formats, TWR_VIS_vvvvv or SFC_VIS_vvvvv, respectively

      • VPV_SV_VSL_PATTERN

        static final Pattern VPV_SV_VSL_PATTERN
        Variable Prevailing Visibility (VIS_vnvn vnvnVvxvxvx vxvx). Variable prevailing visibility shall be coded in the format VIS_vn vnvnvnVvxvx vxvxvx Sector Visibility (VIS_[DIR]_vvvvv){Plain Language]. The sector visibility shall be coded in the format VIS_[DIR]_vvvvv Visibility At Second Location (VIS_vvvvv_[LOC]). At designated automated stations, the visibility at a second location shall be coded in the format VIS_vvvvv_[LOC] visibility shall be coded in the formats, TWR_VIS_vvvvv or SFC_VIS_vvvvv, respectively

      • LIGHTNING_PATTERN

        static final Pattern LIGHTNING_PATTERN
        Lightning (Frequency_LTG(type)_[LOC]).

      • TS_CLD_LOC_PATTERN

        static final Pattern TS_CLD_LOC_PATTERN
        Thunderstorm Location (TS_LOC_(MOV_DIR)) [Plain Language]. Thunderstorm(s) shall be coded in the format, TS_LOC_(MOV_DIR) Significant Cloud Types - Cumulonimbus (CB), Towering Cumulus (TCU), Altocumulus Castellanus (ACC) Cumulonimbus Mammatus (CBMAM), Virga (VIRGA)

      • PRECIP_3HR_24HR_PATTERN

        static final Pattern PRECIP_3HR_24HR_PATTERN
        3- and 6-hour Precipitation (6RRRR). At designated stations, the 3- and 6-hourly precipitation group shall be coded in the format 6RRRR 24-Hour Precipitation Amount (7R24R24 R24R24). At designated stations, the 24-hour precipitation amount shall be coded in the format, 7R24R24R24R24

      • TEMP_1HR_PATTERN

        static final Pattern TEMP_1HR_PATTERN
        Hourly Temperature and Dew Point (TsnT'T'T'snT'dT'dT'd). At designated stations, the hourly temperature and dew point group shall be coded to the tenth of a degree Celsius in the format, TsnT'T'T'snT'dT'dT'd

      • TEMP_24HR_PATTERN

        static final Pattern TEMP_24HR_PATTERN
        24-Hour Maximum and Minimum Temperature 4snTxTxTxsnTnTnTn; tenth of degree Celsius; reported at midnight local standard time; 1 if temperature below 0°C and 0 if temperature 0°C or higher, e.g., 400461006.

      • AUTOMATED_MAINTENANCE_PATTERN

        static final Pattern AUTOMATED_MAINTENANCE_PATTERN
        Automated Maintenance Data RVRNO: RVR missing; PWINO: precipitation identifier information not available; PNO: precipitation amount not available; FZRANO: freezing rain information not available; TSNO: thunderstorm information not available (may indicate augmenting weather observer not logged on); VISNO [LOC]: visibility at second location not available, e.g. VISNO RWY06; CHINO [LOC]: (cloud-height- indicator) sky condition at secondary location not available, e.g., CHINO RWY06. $: Maintenance check indicator ASOS requires maintenance
